@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy - INDOR";
    Layout = null;
    ViewBag.OnboardingShowBack = true;
}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no" />
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.0/css/all.min.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/onboarding.css" asp-append-version="true" />
</head>
<body class="ob-page ob-page--white">
    <div class="ob-shell">
        <div class="ob-shell-inner">
            @await Html.PartialAsync("_OnboardingNav")

            <article class="ob-legal-doc">
                <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
                <p class="ob-legal-updated">Last updated: May 2026</p>

                <p>Home Indor Technology Inc (&ldquo;INDOR&rdquo;, &ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use the INDOR platform.</p>

                <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
                <p>We may collect account information (such as your name, email, phone number, and password), property address and related home profile data, documents you upload, service requests, usage data, and technical information such as device type and log data.</p>

                <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
                <p>We use your information to create and manage your account, build your home profile, provide app features (including House Facts, documents, services, and maintenance), improve our platform, communicate with you, and comply with legal obligations.</p>

                <h2>3. Property &amp; Enrichment Data</h2>
                <p>When you search for a property address, INDOR may retrieve and store property-related information from public records and licensed data providers to populate your home profile. This helps deliver accurate house facts and related features.</p>

                <h2>4. Sharing of Information</h2>
                <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share data with service providers who help us operate the platform, with third parties when you request a service through INDOR, or when required by law.</p>

                <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
                <p>We retain your information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide services, resolve disputes, and meet legal requirements. You may request deletion of your information through account settings where available.</p>

                <h2>6. Security</h2>
                <p>We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures to protect your information. No method of transmission or storage is completely secure.</p>

                <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
                <p>Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or restrict processing of your personal information. You can review or update much of your information within the app.</p>

                <h2>8. Children</h2>
                <p>INDOR is not intended for users under 18 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

                <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
                <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post the revised policy with an updated date. Continued use of INDOR after changes constitutes acceptance.</p>

                <h2>10. Contact</h2>
                <p>For privacy-related questions, contact Home Indor Technology Inc through the support options available in the app.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
